Layout Proposal: Dashboard Overview, Daily Activity, and Sidebar

Document Version: 1.0
Date: March 26, 2026
Author: Manus AI

1. Introduction

This document details the layout proposal for the initial build of the HR dashboard, focusing on the Dashboard Overview, Daily Activity section, and the primary Sidebar Navigation. This proposal adheres to the Visual Design Language document, incorporating its defined color palettes, typography, and UI component styles to ensure a cohesive, modern, and intuitive user experience.

2. Overall Dashboard Layout

The dashboard will adopt a fixed sidebar layout with a persistent top header, providing a consistent navigation experience while maximizing the content area. The main content will be presented in a flexible, grid-based structure, allowing for responsive adaptation across various screen sizes.

Component
Description
Styling Considerations (Tailwind CSS Examples)
Sidebar
Fixed to the left, containing primary navigation links. Collapsible to provide more screen real estate.
fixed, left-0, top-0, h-screen, bg-white (Light Mode), w-64 (expanded), w-20 (collapsed), shadow-lg (subtle)
Top Header
Spans the width of the content area, positioned above the main content. Contains global actions and user-specific elements.
fixed, top-0, right-0, h-16, bg-white (Light Mode), shadow-md, z-10
Main Content Area
Occupies the remaining space, dynamically adjusting based on sidebar state. Houses the dashboard overview and module-specific content.
ml-64 (when sidebar expanded), ml-20 (when sidebar collapsed), pt-16 (to clear header), bg-slate-50 (Light Mode), p-6




3. Sidebar Navigation

The sidebar will be a clean, minimalist component designed for easy access to core HR modules. Its design will prioritize readability and clear visual hierarchy.

Element
Description
Styling Considerations (Tailwind CSS Examples)
Logo/Brand Area
Top section of the sidebar, displaying the company logo.
h-16, flex, items-center, justify-center, border-b, border-slate-200
Navigation Links
List of primary links: Users, Time Clock, Schedule. Each link will have an icon and text label.
flex, items-center, py-3, px-4, text-slate-800, font-semibold, hover:bg-indigo-50, hover:text-indigo-600
Active Link State
Visually distinct styling for the currently active navigation link.
bg-indigo-100, text-indigo-700, border-l-4, border-indigo-500
Icons
Line-based or filled icons consistent with the chosen icon library (e.g., Heroicons).
w-6, h-6, mr-3
Collapsible Functionality
A toggle mechanism to expand or collapse the sidebar, revealing or hiding text labels.
transition-all, duration-300, ease-in-out




4. Top Header

The top header will provide essential global functionalities and user context, maintaining a clean and uncluttered appearance.

Element
Description
Styling Considerations (Tailwind CSS Examples)
Global Search Bar
An input field for searching across the entire dashboard (employees, schedules, etc.).
w-64, p-2, rounded-md, border, border-slate-200, focus:ring-indigo-500
Location Switcher
A dropdown for managers to select and switch between different store locations.
relative, inline-block, text-slate-700, hover:text-indigo-600
User Profile/Avatar
Displays the logged-in user's avatar and name, with a dropdown for settings/logout.
flex, items-center, space-x-2, cursor-pointer
Notifications Icon
An icon indicating new notifications, with a badge for unread counts.
relative, text-slate-700, hover:text-indigo-600




5. Dashboard Overview Layout

The Dashboard Overview will be the landing page, providing a high-level summary of key HR metrics and daily activities. It will utilize a grid-based, card-centric design.

Section
Description
Styling Considerations (Tailwind CSS Examples)
Welcome/Greeting
A personalized greeting for the logged-in user.
text-2xl, font-bold, text-slate-800, mb-6
Metric Cards (Top Row)
A series of prominent cards displaying key performance indicators (e.g., Total Employees, Active Now, Late Arrivals).
grid, grid-cols-1 (mobile), md:grid-cols-2, lg:grid-cols-4, gap-6, mb-6
Store Overview Cards
A grid of cards, each representing a store location with summary metrics (as per Connecteam reference).
grid, grid-cols-1 (mobile), md:grid-cols-2, lg:grid-cols-3, gap-6, mb-6
Main Charts Section
Area for larger data visualizations, such as attendance trends or labor cost breakdowns.
grid, grid-cols-1 (mobile), lg:grid-cols-2, gap-6, mb-6
Daily Activity Section
A dedicated area for real-time updates and an operational snapshot.
col-span-full (full width on smaller screens), lg:col-span-1 (side-by-side with charts on larger screens)




6. Daily Activity Section Layout

This section will provide a dynamic feed of recent events and a quick operational summary for the current day.

Element
Description
Styling Considerations (Tailwind CSS Examples)
Operational Snapshot Widget
A card displaying real-time metrics (Scheduled, Late Clock-ins, Clocked in now, Total Attendance, Late Clock-outs).
bg-white, rounded-lg, shadow-md, p-4, mb-4
Activity Feed List
A scrollable list of recent employee actions (clock-ins, clock-outs, PTO requests).
bg-white, rounded-lg, shadow-md, p-4, h-96 (fixed height with scroll), overflow-y-auto
Activity Item
Each item in the feed, showing event, employee, and timestamp.
flex, items-center, py-2, border-b, border-slate-100, last:border-b-0




This layout proposal, combined with the Visual Design Language, provides a clear direction for the aesthetic and structural development of the HR dashboard, ensuring a beautiful and functional initial build.

